<section id="block-cgdw3css-content" class="w3-block w3-block-wrapper block-system block-system-main-block">
  
    
      <article data-history-node-id="3130472" about="/staff/rory-todd" class="w3-row node node--type-expert node--view-mode-full">
  <div class="node__content">
    <div id="expert-content-left">
      <div class="expandable">
                          <div id="expert-bio">
            <h4>Bio</h4>
            
            <div class="field field--name-field-desc4 field--type-text-long field--label-hidden w3-clear w3-bar-item field__item"><p>Rory is a Research Assistant with the Global Education team. Prior to joining CGD, he worked as a research assistant at the University of Manchester, measuring the impact of Covid-19 lockdown restrictions on economic hardship. Rory is from London and has an MSc in Social Research Methods and Statistics from the University of Manchester, where his dissertation explored patterns in knife crime using spatial models. Previously he received a BA in History from Durham University.</p>
</div>
      
          </div>
              </div>
      <div class="expand-button-wrapper">
        <div class="expand-button">Expand<i class="fa fa-angle-double-down"></i></div>
        <div class="collapse-button">Collapse<i class="fa fa-angle-double-up"></i></div>
      </div>
